  introContent={`
    <p>Sukkur Electric Power Company (SEPCO) supplies electricity to over 2.4 million consumers across upper Sindh and two Balochistan districts. Established in 2010 by separating from HESCO, SEPCO covers: <strong>Sukkur</strong>, <strong>Larkana</strong>, <strong>Khairpur</strong>, <strong>Ghotki</strong>, <strong>Jacobabad</strong>, <strong>Shikarpur</strong>, <strong>Kamber Shahdadkot</strong>, <strong>Kashmore Kandhkot</strong>, and parts of Dadu and Naushehro Feroze. SEPCO also extends into <strong>Jafarabad</strong> and <strong>Naseerabad</strong> districts of Balochistan — making it the only DISCO that crosses a provincial boundary.</p>
    <p><strong>Sukkur</strong> — SEPCO's headquarters city — sits at the crossroads of upper Sindh and is one of Pakistan's oldest cities, home to the historic Sukkur Barrage that controls irrigation for millions of acres. <strong>Larkana</strong> is the native city of the Bhutto political family and a major agricultural and commercial centre. <strong>Khairpur</strong> is famous for its dates — Pakistan's largest date-growing district. <strong>Ghotki</strong> is home to major fertilizer and chemical industries. These industries make SEPCO a critical industrial electricity supplier for northern Sindh's economy.</p>
    <p>SEPCO is a younger DISCO than HESCO — created in 2010 specifically because HESCO's territory was too large to manage effectively. SEPCO uses the same <strong>14-digit reference number system</strong> on the same PITC server as all other WAPDA DISCOs. Enter your reference number in the bill checker above to view your complete bill instantly. If you live in Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, or Thatta, check our <a href="/hesco-bill/">HESCO bill page</a> — those areas are HESCO, not SEPCO.</p>
  
    <p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering all 19 utility providers. Also check: <a href="/hesco-bill/">HESCO bill</a> for Hyderabad | <a href="/qesco-bill/">QESCO bill</a> for Balochistan | <a href="/ssgc-bill/">SSGC gas bill</a>. Use our <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/">electricity bill calculator</a>, visit our <a href="/dashboard/">bill dashboard</a>, or read about <a href="/blog/fpa-charges-explained/">FPA charges explained</a>. See our <a href="/sukkur/">Sukkur utility bills guide</a>.</p>
  `}
