  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my SEPCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit SEPCO reference number in the bill checker above and click Check Bill. Your complete SEPCO electricity bill for Sukkur, Larkana, Khairpur, or any upper Sindh district appears in seconds. Free, no login, 24/7." },
    { question: "What is the difference between SEPCO and HESCO?", answer: "SEPCO covers upper Sindh: Sukkur, Larkana, Khairpur, Ghotki, Jacobabad, Shikarpur, and Kamber. HESCO covers lower Sindh: Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Thatta, Badin, and Nawabshah. SEPCO was separated from HESCO in 2010. Your bill heading clearly states which company you belong to." },
    { question: "Does SEPCO cover areas in Balochistan?", answer: "Yes. SEPCO supplies Jafarabad district (Usta Muhammad, Gandawa) and Naseerabad district (Tamboo, Chattar) in Balochistan. Despite being geographically in Balochistan, these consumers use SEPCO — not QESCO. Check your bill heading to confirm." },
    { question: "How do I check SEPCO bill for Larkana?", answer: "Larkana is under SEPCO's Larkana Circle. Enter your 14-digit SEPCO reference number in the checker above — it works for all Larkana, Ratodero, Naudero, and Dokri consumers. The same tool works for all SEPCO districts." },
    { question: "How do I download my SEPCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After your bill loads, click Download PDF and select Save as PDF. Your SEPCO duplicate bill saves instantly — ready to pay at Easypaisa or JazzCash anywhere in Sukkur, Larkana, or upper Sindh." },
    { question: "How do I pay my SEPCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank app. Select Electricity, choose SEPCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify amount, and confirm. Easypaisa and JazzCash are widely available across upper Sindh." },
    { question: "Why is my SEPCO bill not received by post?", answer: "Rural upper Sindh has unreliable postal delivery. Your bill is generated on the SEPCO/PITC system every month even if it never physically arrives. Use this tool monthly to check your bill and due date — your obligation to pay exists regardless of whether a paper bill arrived." },
    { question: "What is SEPCO's grace period?", answer: "SEPCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After 7 days, a 10% surcharge applies. Check your due date online using this tool — do not wait for a paper bill in areas with unreliable delivery." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with SEPCO?", answer: "Call 071-5633605 or 118 with your reference number. Get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). SEPCO must resolve within 14 working days. Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 if ignored." },
